<div class="comments-body">
<p>I remember trying the Brain some years ago when it first came out. I first checked it out because of the cool transitional effect that happened when you navigated to a different node. My problem with the Brain was that it didn't show enough information at once, and that the transitions themselves were disorienting.</p>

<p>When I'm trying to "refactor" my mind dumps, I find that there are times where I need to integrate information from sub-trees that are separated by large numbers of nodes. I find that I want to run FreeMind across both of my monitors at once (although it doesn't support this very well).</p>
